The NASA co-principals have been urged to join President Uhuru Kenyatta and Opposition leader Raila Odinga in uniting the country. Devolution Cabinet Secretary Eugene Wamalwa (pictured) criticised the decision by Ford Kenya leader Moses Wetang'ula and his ANC counterpart, Musalia Mudavadi, to form a political party for the western region. ALSO READ:

Uhuru-Raila reconciliation offers valuable lessons for troubled Great Lakes region "We want politics that unite the country not divide communities," said Mr Wamalwa, adding: "If it means uniting then let the entire western region unite." He said even if the agenda to push for Luhya unity was to field a presidential candidate in 2022, the region would still need other communities to win.